  "title": "Venezuela Just Had Its Worst Earthquake in Over a Century",
  "script": "Two earthquakes. Forty seconds apart! On Wednesday evening, Venezuela was hit by a 7.2-magnitude quake. Then — 40 seconds later — a 7.5. Before rescue teams could even mobilize from the first. The coastal state of La Guaira, north of Caracas, is now a declared disaster zone: dozens of buildings collapsed, the main airport shut down, roads cut off. The acting president confirmed at least 164 dead. The U.S. Geological Survey says the actual toll could exceed 10,000. It could top 100,000. Rescue teams from the US, Dominican Republic, and Mexico are on their way. Venezuela hasn't seen an earthquake this powerful in over a century. And the 40-second gap meant the second one hit while people were still inside buildings from the first. Will the La Guaira death toll be the final number, or just the starting point?",
